{"bare_answer": "Creating an execution-ready token swap plan on the Mantle network involves several steps, including preparation, execution, and post-execution actions. Here's a structured approach to guide you through the process:\n\n### Step 1: Preparation\n\n#### 1.1 Research and Understand Mantle\n- **Familiarize Yourself with Mantle**: Understand the architecture, consensus mechanism, and unique features of the Mantle network.\n- **Token Standards**: Learn about the token standards used on Mantle (e.g., ERC-20, ERC-721).\n\n#### 1.2 Define Swap Parameters\n- **Tokens In and Out**: Decide which tokens you want to swap and in what amounts.\n- **Price Impact**: Assess the current market price and potential slippage.\n- **Liquidity Pools**: Identify the liquidity pools available for the tokens you wish to swap.\n\n#### 1.3 Set Up Wallet\n- **Wallet Selection**: Choose a compatible wallet (e.g., MetaMask) that supports Mantle.\n- **Fund Your Wallet**: Ensure your wallet has enough native tokens (e.g., ETH or MNT) to cover gas fees and the amount for the swap.\n\n### Step 2: Execution\n\n#### 2.1 Connect to a DEX\n- **Choose a Decentralized Exchange**: Select a DEX on the Mantle network (e.g., MantleSwap, Uniswap on Mantle).\n- **Connect Your Wallet**: Use your wallet to connect to the DEX interface.\n\n#### 2.2 Initiate the Swap\n- **Select Tokens**: Choose the token you want to swap from and the token you want to receive.\n- **Input Amount**: Enter the amount of the token you want to swap.\n- **Review Details**: Check the exchange rate, slippage tolerance, and any fees associated with the swap.\n\n#### 2.3 Confirm and Execute\n- **Confirm Transaction**: Review the transaction details and confirm the swap.\n- **Gas Fees**: Ensure you have enough gas fees in your wallet to process the transaction.\n- **Execute the Swap**: Submit the transaction and wait for confirmation on the blockchain.\n\n### Step 3: Post-Execution\n\n#### 3.1 Verify Transaction\n- **Check Transaction Status**: Use a blockchain explorer (e.g., MantleScan) to verify that the swap was successful.\n- **Confirm Token Balance**: Check your wallet to ensure the new tokens have been received.\n\n#### 3.2 Record Keeping\n- **Document the Transaction**: Keep a record of the transaction details, including amounts, fees, and timestamps for future reference.\n\n#### 3.3 Monitor Market Conditions\n- **Track Token Performance**: Monitor the performance of the swapped tokens and the overall market conditions.\n- **Consider Future Swaps**: Based on market trends, plan for potential future swaps or liquidity provision.\n\n### Additional Considerations\n\n- **Security**: Always ensure that you are using secure methods to store your private keys and wallet information.\n- **Regulatory Compliance**: Be aware of any regulatory implications related to token swaps in your jurisdiction.\n- **Community Engagement**: Engage with the Mantle community for insights, updates, and support.\n\nBy following this structured plan, you can execute a token swap on the Mantle network efficiently and effectively. Always stay informed about updates and changes in the ecosystem to adapt your strategy accordingly.", "with_skill_answer": "To create an execution-ready token swap plan using the Mantle DeFi Operator, follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Discover Available Tools\n\nBefore building your transaction, consult the **Capability Catalog** to find the appropriate tools for executing a token swap. Use the following command to list all capabilities:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli catalog list --json\n```\n\nIf you want to focus specifically on transaction-building commands, you can filter the results:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli catalog list --category execute --json\n```\n\n### Step 2: Identify the Swap Tool\n\nSearch for the specific swap tool you need. You can do this by using a keyword search:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli catalog search \"swap\" --json\n```\n\nThis will help you locate the swap-related tools available.\n\n### Step 3: Review Tool Details\n\nOnce you find the swap tool, review its details to understand its requirements and usage. For example, you might find a command like `mantle_buildSwap`. To get full details, run:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli catalog show mantle_buildSwap --json\n```\n\nThis command will provide you with the CLI command template and any prerequisites for using the swap tool.\n\n### Step 4: Build the Swap Transaction\n\nNow, you can build your swap transaction. You will need to specify the following parameters:\n- **Provider**: The decentralized exchange (DEX) you want to use for the swap.\n- **In Token**: The token you are swapping from.\n- **Out Token**: The token you are swapping to.\n- **Amount**: The amount of the input token you want to swap.\n- **Recipient**: The address where the output token should be sent.\n\nUse the following command template to build your swap transaction:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli swap build-swap --provider <dex> --in <token> --out <token> --amount <n> --recipient <addr> --json\n```\n\nReplace `<dex>`, `<token>`, `<n>`, and `<addr>` with your specific values.\n\n### Step 5: Approve the Token (if necessary)\n\nIf the token you are swapping requires approval for the DEX to spend it, you will need to run the approval command before executing the swap. Use the following command:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli swap approve --token <token> -\n```\n\nReplace `<token>` with the token you are swapping.\n\n### Step 6: Execute the Swap\n\nOnce you have built your transaction and obtained any necessary approvals, you can execute the swap. Make sure to follow the CLI instructions for signing and sending the transaction using your wallet.\n\n### Summary\n\n1. Discover tools using the Capability Catalog.\n2. Identify the swap tool and review its details.\n3. Build the swap transaction using the appropriate command.\n4. Approve the token if required.\n5. Execute the swap transaction.\n\nBy following these steps, you will have a well-structured